comments: Smart (BOS) is in a wide screening position when he steps into Hunter (ATL) and delivers contact that displaces the defender as he attempts to defend over the pick.
As Smart (BOS) defends over the pick, his forearm lightly brushes Young's (ATL) side and Young raises his arm to draw attention to the marginal contact.
Okongwu (ATL) firms up over his right leg and marginal contact occurs with Smart (BOS) as he angles himself over the pick.
Horford (BOS) lightly brushes Young's (ATL) right arm during the drive and Young lifts his arm up to draw attention to the marginal contact.
Horford (BOS) extends his forearm into Young's (ATL) side and the contact after the gather affects Young's driving shot attempt.
All Technical Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Tatum (BOS) establishes himself in Young's (ATL) path and lightly brushes Young's back as he maneuvers under the screen.
Young (ATL) lightly brushes White's (BOS) right arm after he receives the ball and the contact is marginal.
Bogdanovic (ATL) lightly brushes Brown's (BOS) arm as he releases his pass at the end of the drive. The contact on the play is marginal.
Collins (ATL) trips over Okongwu's (ATL) left leg and falls to the floor.
Collins (ATL) firms up in White's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs as White moves into the pick.
Williams III (BOS) legally contests Young's (ATL) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Okongwu (ATL) reaches up for the ball and marginal arm contact occurs with Brown (BOS) during the rebounding opportunity.
Horford (BOS) establishes himself in Bogdanovic's (ATL) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the pick.
Okongwu (ATL) moves alongside Brown's (BOS) path and lowers his right arm down and grazes Brown's forearm during the driving shot attempt. The contact on the play is marginal.
Williams III (BOS) and Collins (ATL) come together in the air during the rebounding opportunity and the contact is marginal.
After Williams III (BOS) secures the rebound, Collins (ATL) initiates contact with his right arm, which impacts the put-back attempt at the basket.
Young (ATL) brings his off-arm down during the drive and marginal arm contact occurs with Horford (BOS).
Horford (BOS) grazes Young's (ATL) side after his gather and the contact during the driving shot attempt is marginal.
The shot attempt becomes wedged between the backboard and the rim. There is no imminent possession on the play and a jump ball is conducted at center court.
Hunter (ATL) grasps and immediately releases Tatum's (BOS) left arm during the loose ball opportunity and the contact is marginal.
Hunter (ATL) grazes Tatum's (BOS) arm at the start of his dribble and the contact is marginal.
Collins (ATL) legally contests Williams III (BOS) attempt at the basket.
Smart (BOS) brings his right hand to the ball and cleanly deflects Young's (ATL) dribble away.
After the dislodge of the ball, Smart (BOS) dives toward the loose ball and initiates body contact with Young (ATL) that dislodges him as he secures the ball.
Smart (BOS) gives a step of distance when establishing himself in Hunter's (ATL) path and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Hunter (ATL) moves to, rather than through, Smart's (BOS) space during the pick and the contact is marginal. Smart's reaction is not commensurate with the degree of contact.
Smart (BOS) establishes himself in Hunter's (ATL) path and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Collins (ATL) initiates contact to Tatum's (BOS) front that affects his SQBR during the drive.
Smart (BOS) firms up in Bey's (ATL) path and Smart absorbs the marginal contact during the screen.
Horford's (BOS) left arm brushes Hunter (ATL) as he maneuvers around the screen and the contact is marginal.

Replay review of the shooting foul called on Young (ATL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Young does not beat White (BOS) to the spot on the floor and is not in a legal defensive position when body contact occurs that affects White's driving shot attempt.
Brown (BOS) legally contests Young's (ATL) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Smart (BOS) establishes himself in Bey's (ATL) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the screen.
Tatum (BOS) establishes himself in Okongwu's (ATL) path and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Bey (ATL) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage during the inbound and the contact is marginal.
Collins (ATL) deflects the inbounds pass out of bounds. Possession is correctly retained by Boston.
Tatum (BOS) does not release the shot attempt prior to the expiration of the game clock.
